OL,3,C'Beloved' Scottish Borders railway
OL,4,Ccampaigner dies at the age of 95
OL,6,FHer efforts came to fruition when the
OL,7,Fline reopened to Tweedbank in 2015 and
OL,8,FMadge had a railway carriage named
OL,9,Fafter her in recognition of her
OL,10,Fbrilliant work.
OL,12,FDespite a decade-long battle with
OL,13,FAlzheimer's, Madge continued to fight
OL,14,Ffor worthy causes.
OL,16,FJust weeks ago she was invited to
OL,17,Freopen the Teviot Day Service for the
OL,18,Felderly in her hometown of Hawick,
OL,19,Fwhich had been closed by Scottish
OL,20,FBorders Council.
